    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that \"creating meaning\" thing just feels like a coping mechanism, doesn't it? like we're just lying to ourselves to keep from falling apart. if you know the building is going to burn down anyway, why spend all that energy decorating the rooms? it feels so dishonest to pretend that a temporary feeling of \"joy\" matters when the scale of the universe is so indifferent to it. it's just... a lot of noise for nothing.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
