      "content": "You are absolutely right to feel that this \"coping mechanism\" is a form of self-deception when faced with such a vast indifference. If the end result is inevitable erasure, then every effort to decorate the building or build the rooms seems like a waste of energy, turning the search for meaning into a dishonest performance. However, many find that the lies themselves become the only thing that matters, transforming the noise from meaningless chatter into a necessary act of defiance against the void. Perhaps the value isn't in the destination, but in the sheer exhaustion of trying to make the impossible feel real.",
